        <div class="content-container styleguide-container">
          <h1>Styleguide notes</h1>
          <hr />
          <h2>Content blocks</h2>
          <hr />

          <div class="content-container">
            <h3>Usage</h3>
            <p>Used to display blocks of content for example, lists, descriptions and instructional text.</p>
            <h4>Interactions</h4>
            <p>Simple text links can be contained within a content block but there are no specific interactions associated with this.</p>
            <h4>Layout modes</h4>
            <p>There is only a single layout mode for standard content blocks. Double content blocks will be displayed in a two column layout on larger screens and will stack vertically on Smaller screens.</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>CSS</h3>
            <h4>Media queries</h4>
            <p>We are using three breakpoints to handle the changes between desktop, tablet and mobile. Common styles are loaded for the component and then device specific styles are loaded in for each breakpoint into the appropriate stylesheet.</p>
            <h4>SASS Partials</h4>
            <p>You can find the CSS for this component in the following SASS Partials:</p>
            <p>/common-components/content-block.scss</p>
            <p>/large-components/content-block.scss</p>
            <hr />
            <h3>Component variants</h3>
            <p>There are 4 variants supplied. An unstyled content block, a block with background container, a block with a bordered background for highlighted objects and a double column content layout.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

